## ❌ What's Missing (Gap Analysis)

### 🔴 CRITICAL GAPS — These Block Production Use

#### 1. **Authentication & Authorization** — COMPLETELY ABSENT
- No JWT auth, no login/register, no user table
- Anyone can access any dataset via any URL
- No dataset ownership check

#### 2. **Background Task Queue (Redis + Celery)** — MISSING
- Pipeline runs synchronously — **60-second timeout risk** on large files
- No progress tracking (SSE stream)
- No task retry on failure
- No pipeline status stored in DB

#### 3. **Real RAG Pipeline** — MISSING
- ChromaDB is initialized but **nothing is actually stored in it**
- FAISS stores query history but is **not used for retrieval-augmented generation**
- No document chunking, no retrieval pipeline feeding context to LLM
- What exists: FAISS for query deduplication — **NOT a real RAG pipeline**

#### 4. **LLM Insight Generation Disabled**
- `use_llm=False` hardcoded in [orchestrator.py](file:///c:/Users/HP/OneDrive/Desktop/Talking%20BI/talking-bi/backend/agents/orchestrator.py) line 157
- Insight agent only uses rule-based patterns
- LLM narration of insights = **zero** currently

#### 5. **Startup Validation Missing**
- No API key check on startup
- No DB health check
- No PIPELINE_LOCK semaphore (concurrent uploads can corrupt state)

---

### 🟡 IMPORTANT GAPS — Big Moat Features Missing

#### 6. **FireDucks / DuckDB** — NOT INTEGRATED
- Currently using Pandas for all data ops
- **FireDucks** (pandas drop-in, 10–100x faster via JIT) = not installed
- **DuckDB** (columnar SQL engine, handles 50M+ rows) = not installed
- Large file performance would bottleneck at ~500K rows with current Pandas

#### 7. **Indian Localization** — MISSING
- No Rs/L/Cr number formatting
- No Indian FY (April–March) grouping
- No GST column auto-detection
- No Hindi language mode
- This is the **core market differentiator** from the prompt spec

#### 8. **LangGraph State Machine** — NOT USED
- Agents are called sequentially in plain Python ([orchestrator.py](file:///c:/Users/HP/OneDrive/Desktop/Talking%20BI/talking-bi/backend/agents/orchestrator.py))
- No LangGraph `StateGraph`, no typed `AgentState`, no conditional routing
- Routing logic is `if plan.get("kpis"):` — not a proper state machine

#### 9. **Forecast Agent** — MISSING
- No time-series prediction endpoint
- No LinearRegression + moving average fallback forecasting
- Root cause agent exists but forecast = absent

#### 10. **Conversation Agent (Multi-turn)** — MISSING
- Query memory exists in SQLite but no sliding-window conversation context
- Each NL query is stateless — no reference to prior turns
- "What about last year?" after "Show revenue by region" = broken

#### 11. **Doc2Chart Agent** — MISSING
- Only CSV/Excel are processed
- No PDF table extraction (pdfplumber = installed but unused for upload)
- No DOCX table extraction
- No image OCR (pytesseract not installed)

#### 12. **Alert Engine** — MISSING
- No threshold alerts ("alert if revenue < 50K")
- No consecutive decline detection
- No anomaly alert triggers
- Anomaly detection exists in ML service but no alert system

#### 13. **Dataset Diff** — MISSING
- No endpoint to compare two datasets side-by-side
- No schema diff, no KPI delta table, no overlaid charts

#### 14. **Voice Query** — MISSING
- No Whisper integration
- No mic input on frontend
- Not even planned in current routes

#### 15. **InsightEval Agent** — MISSING
- Insight agent generates insights but **no validator** checks numbers
- LLM could hallucinate "Revenue grew 500%" when actual = 12%
- Taxonomy check, number validation, novelty dedup = all absent

#### 16. **Ollama / Privacy Mode** — MISSING
- All LLM calls go to Groq (cloud)
- No local fallback for sensitive data (CA firms, hospitals)
- `LLM_PROVIDER` env switch = not implemented

---

### 🟢 NICE-TO-HAVE GAPS — Competitive Moat

#### 17. **Story Mode** — MISSING
- No 3-paragraph executive narrative endpoint
- Report agent generates full reports but no lightweight story endpoint

#### 18. **MongoDB** — NOT USED (Using SQLite)
- Schema shows [Dataset](file:///c:/Users/HP/OneDrive/Desktop/Talking%20BI/talking-bi/backend/database/models.py#9-23), [Dashboard](file:///c:/Users/HP/OneDrive/Desktop/Talking%20BI/talking-bi/backend/database/models.py#25-38), etc. in SQLite
- For multi-user + large scale: MongoDB/GridFS better
- Current: SQLite works fine for MVP, needs migration for scale

#### 19. **Docker Compose** — MISSING
- No `docker-compose.yml`
- No containerization for backend/frontend/redis/celery
- Manual setup required

#### 20. **EvalAgent (Pipeline QA)** — MISSING
- No confidence score on dashboard header
- No schema accuracy checker running post-pipeline
- Critic agent exists but doesn't do full pipeline QA

#### 21. **DeepPrep with Quality Score** — PARTIAL
- Cleaning agent does 6 steps but no `quality_score` computed after each step
- No step revert if score drops
- No fuzzy category merge (fuzzywuzzy installed but not used in cleaning)

#### 22. **Tests** — MINIMAL
- [test_dashboard_api.py](file:///c:/Users/HP/OneDrive/Desktop/Talking%20BI/talking-bi/backend/test_dashboard_api.py), [test_data_flow.py](file:///c:/Users/HP/OneDrive/Desktop/Talking%20BI/talking-bi/backend/test_data_flow.py), [test_fixes.py](file:///c:/Users/HP/OneDrive/Desktop/Talking%20BI/talking-bi/backend/test_fixes.py) exist
- No sample data generator with injected edge cases
- No mock LLM test for InsightEval
- No CI pipeline

